    <!-- Chosen Palette: Warm Neutrals with Muted Greens/Blues for Comfort and Focus (Neuroscience-based) -->
    <!-- Application Structure Plan: The application is structured with a dynamic main content area. It starts with a "Home" section (hero) and includes a "Criar Avatar" section. The core learning content is presented via an interactive "Mapa dos Reinos" (conceptual map) where each "realm" corresponds to a chapter. Clicking a realm on the map or a week on the timeline (which is now part of the realm's detail view) dynamically updates a content area below, displaying detailed learning objectives, key concepts, mini-project (now "Desafio"), suggested books, and YouTube resources. A "Marcar como Concluído" button and a progress bar track user progress via localStorage. A dedicated "Biblioteca de Referências" modal provides a centralized list of recommended books. This structure was chosen to transform the dense, linear text of the source report into a non-linear, engaging, and explorable quest, aligning with the RPG theme and enhancing user motivation and understanding of the overall learning path. -->
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices: 1. Report Info: 25-week curriculum structure. Goal: Organize/Navigate. Viz/Method: Interactive HTML/CSS/JS "Mapa dos Reinos" (conceptual map with clickable "realms") and a timeline within the realm's detail. Interaction: Click on realm/week to display details; visual progress indicator on completed weeks. Justification: Visually represents the learning journey as a "quest," making the plan less intimidating and more engaging than a long text list, with added progress tracking for motivation. 2. Report Info: Breakdown of topics (Python, SQL, etc.). Goal: Inform/Proportions. Viz/Method: Chart.js Donut Chart. Interaction: Hover for tooltips. Justification: Provides a quick, digestible overview of what the course covers. 3. Report Info: Estimated "Pomodoros" per topic. Goal: Compare/Inform. Viz/Method: Chart.js Bar Chart. Interaction: Hover for tooltips. Justification: Helps users understand the relative time commitment for each major skill area. 4. Report Info: Detailed text for each week. Goal: Inform/Elaborate. Viz/Method: Dynamic HTML content blocks with RPG analogies. Interaction: Content appears on-click from the timeline, includes embedded YouTube links and book references. Justification: Breaks down the large volume of text into manageable, on-demand chunks, preventing information overload, and provides direct access to supplementary learning materials, all within the immersive theme. 5. Report Info: Reference books. Goal: Support/Expand. Viz/Method: Modal with HTML list. Interaction: Button to open modal. Justification: Centralizes additional learning resources without cluttering the main page. 6. Report Info: Progress tracking. Goal: Motivate/Track. Viz/Method: HTML/CSS progress bar and "Marcar como Concluído" button. Interaction: Click to update progress, visual feedback on timeline. Justification: Encourages continuous engagement and provides a clear sense of accomplishment. 7. New Feature: Avatar Creation. Goal: Engagement/Personalization. Viz/Method: Canvas drawing with HTML UI controls. Interaction: Select parts to draw avatar, "Salvar" button. Justification: Adds a fun, interactive element that reinforces the RPG theme and personalizes the user's journey. 8. New Feature: Home Page Intro. Goal: Engagement/Onboarding. Viz/Method: HTML/CSS hero section with text and button. Interaction: Click button to start journey. Justification: Provides a welcoming and thematic entry point to the application. -->
    <!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->
